colubrisSystemMIB.name: colubrisSystemMIB
colubrisSystemMIB.contactinfo: Colubris Networks Postal: 200 West Street Ste 300 Waltham, Massachusetts 02451-1121 UNITED STATES Phone: +1 781 684 0001 Fax: +1 781 684 0009 E-mail: cn-snmp@colubris.com
colubrisSystemMIB.description: Generic system information for Colubris Networks devices.

systemProductName.name: systemProductName
systemProductName.description: HP product name for the device.

systemFirmwareRevision.name: systemFirmwareRevision
systemFirmwareRevision.description: Revision number of the device firmware.

systemBootRevision.name: systemBootRevision
systemBootRevision.description: Revision number of the device boot loader.

systemHardwareRevision.name: systemHardwareRevision
systemHardwareRevision.description: Revision number of the system hardware.

systemConfigurationVersion.name: systemConfigurationVersion
systemConfigurationVersion.description: User-defined string to identify the current device configuration. This string could be anything in printable ASCII characters.

systemUpTime.name: systemUpTime
systemUpTime.description: How long the system has been running since its last restart. When this counter reaches its maximum value, it wraps around and starts increasing again from zero.

systemMacAddress.name: systemMacAddress
systemMacAddress.description: MAC address of the device. This information is only returned in a systemHeartbeatNotification event.

systemWanPortIpAddress.name: systemWanPortIpAddress
systemWanPortIpAddress.description: IP address of the device WAN port. This information is only returned in a systemHeartbeatNotification event.

systemProductFlavor.name: systemProductFlavor
systemProductFlavor.description: The product flavor can extend or alter the functionality of a HP product.

systemFirmwareBuildDate.name: systemFirmwareBuildDate
systemFirmwareBuildDate.description: Build date of the device firmware in the format YYYY/MM/DD.

systemCDPOperState.name: systemCDPOperState
systemCDPOperState.description: When True indicates that CDP support is enabled.

systemLLDPOperState.name: systemLLDPOperState
systemLLDPOperState.description: When True indicates that the LLDP agent is started.

systemTimeUpdateMode.name: systemTimeUpdateMode
systemTimeUpdateMode.description: Specifies the method and format used to set the system time. 'manual': Operator must configures the system time parameters manually in the GMT zone. 'sntpUdp': Look for time servers in the systemTimeServerTable in order to synchronize the device system time using SNTP. 'tp': Look for time servers in the systemTimeServerTable in order to synchronize the device system time using the Time Protocol.

systemTimeLostWhenRebooting.name: systemTimeLostWhenRebooting
systemTimeLostWhenRebooting.description: Indicates if the system time is lost after rebooting or not. 'true': Indicates that the system time has been lost. 'false': Indicates that the system time has been kept.

systemTimeDSTOn.name: systemTimeDSTOn
systemTimeDSTOn.description: Specifies if the system time need to be adjusted to compensate for daylight savings. 'true': Adjusts the system time by adding one hour. 'false': Keep the current system time.

systemDate.name: systemDate
systemDate.description: Specifies the current GMT system date when systemTimeUpdateMode attribute is set to 'manual' mode. Reading this attribute will return the current date. Specify year (1995-3000), month (01-12), and day (01-31) in the format YYYY/MM/DD. The '/' character is mandatory between the fields.

systemTimeOfDay.name: systemTimeOfDay
systemTimeOfDay.description: Specifies the current GMT system time when systemTimeUpdateMode attribute is set to 'manual' mode. Specify hour (00-24), minutes (00-59), and seconds (00-59) in the format HH:MM:SS. The ':' character is mandatory between the fields.

systemTimeZone.name: systemTimeZone
systemTimeZone.description: Specifies the current system time zone in the relation to UTC. Specify the direction from UTC (+ or -), hours from UTC (00-14 or 00-12), and minutes from UTC (00 or 30) in the format +/-HH:MM. The '+' or '-' character is mandatory at the beginning of the expression. The ':' character is mandatory between the time fields.

systemTimeServerTable.name: systemTimeServerTable
systemTimeServerTable.description: A table containing the list of SNTP time servers that can be used to synchronize the system time. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent.

systemTimeServerEntry.name: systemTimeServerEntry
systemTimeServerEntry.description: A SNTP time server used to get the device time. systemTimeServerIndex - Uniquely identifies a time server in the table.

systemTimeServerIndex.name: systemTimeServerIndex
systemTimeServerIndex.description: Index of the time server in the systemTimeServerTable.

systemTimeServerAddress.name: systemTimeServerAddress
systemTimeServerAddress.description: Specifies the DNS name or IP address of the time server to use. Setting an entry to a null string will delete the entry.

systemTimeServerNotificationEnabled.name: systemTimeServerNotificationEnabled
systemTimeServerNotificationEnabled.description: Specifies if timeServerFailure notifications are generated.

adminAccessAuthenMode.name: adminAccessAuthenMode
adminAccessAuthenMode.description: Specifies if administrator authentication is performed locally or via a RADIUS server. You must have configured a RADIUS profile and the adminAccessAuthenProfileIndex attribute before you can select a profile or an error will be returned.

adminAccessAuthenProfileIndex.name: adminAccessAuthenProfileIndex
adminAccessAuthenProfileIndex.description: Specifies the RADIUS profile to be used in order to authenticate the administrator. This parameter only applies when the adminAccessAuthenMode is set to 'profile'. When the special value zero is specified, no RADIUS server profile is selected.

adminAccessMaxLoginAttempts.name: adminAccessMaxLoginAttempts
adminAccessMaxLoginAttempts.description: Specifies the number of successive unsuccessful authentications that must occur to generate an adminAccessAuthFailureNotification event.

adminAccessLockOutPeriod.name: adminAccessLockOutPeriod
adminAccessLockOutPeriod.description: Specifies the duration when further login attempts are blocked after adminAccessMaxLoginAttempts has been reached. Setting this value to zero disables the lock out feature.

adminAccessLoginNotificationEnabled.name: adminAccessLoginNotificationEnabled
adminAccessLoginNotificationEnabled.description: Specifies if an adminAccessLoginNotification event is generated after an administrator is successfully authenticated.

adminAccessAuthFailureNotificationEnable.name: adminAccessAuthFailureNotificationEnabled
adminAccessAuthFailureNotificationEnable.description: Specifies if an adminAccessAuthFailureNotification event is generated when the number of successive unsuccessful authentications attempts exceed the value of adminAccessMaxLoginAttempts.

adminAccessInfo.name: adminAccessInfo
adminAccessInfo.description: Contains various information about the administrator. This parameter is used in the adminAccessAuthFailureNotification event to return the administrator status to a management system.

adminAccessProfileTable.name: adminAccessProfileTable
adminAccessProfileTable.description: This table handles the profile of several administrator users. In tabular form in order to allow multiple instances on an agent.

adminAccessProfileEntry.name: adminAccessProfileEntry
adminAccessProfileEntry.description: An administrator profile configured in the administrator access table.

adminAccessProfileIndex.name: adminAccessProfileIndex
adminAccessProfileIndex.description: Specifies the index of the administrator profile.

adminAccessUserName.name: adminAccessUserName
adminAccessUserName.description: Specifies the user name of the administrator.

adminAccessAdministrativeRights.name: adminAccessAdministrativeRights
adminAccessAdministrativeRights.description: Specifies the administrative rights of this specific administrator.

adminAccessLogoutNotificationEnabled.name: adminAccessLogoutNotificationEnabled
adminAccessLogoutNotificationEnabled.description: Specifies if an adminAccessLogoutNotification event is generated after an administrator logs out from the web interface.

heartbeatPeriod.name: heartbeatPeriod
heartbeatPeriod.description: Specifies the delay between 2 heartbeat notifications. The range of this parameter is 30 seconds to 1 year.

heartbeatNotificationEnabled.name: heartbeatNotificationEnabled
heartbeatNotificationEnabled.description: Specifies if systemHeartbeatNotification events are generated.

adminAccessAuthFailureNotification.name: adminAccessAuthFailureNotification
adminAccessAuthFailureNotification.description: Sent after an administrator authentication failure.

adminAccessLoginNotification.name: adminAccessLoginNotification
adminAccessLoginNotification.description: Sent after an administrator is successfully authenticated.

adminAccessLogoutNotification.name: adminAccessLogoutNotification
adminAccessLogoutNotification.description: Sent after an administrator has logout.

timeServerFailure.name: timeServerFailure
timeServerFailure.description: Sent when a time server in the system time table is unreachable.

colubrisSystemMIBCompliance.name: colubrisSystemMIBCompliance
colubrisSystemMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Colubris Networks System MIB.

colubrisSystemMIBComplianceDeprecated.name: colubrisSystemMIBComplianceDeprecated
colubrisSystemMIBComplianceDeprecated.description: The compliance statement for deprecated entities which implement the Colubris Networks System MIB.

colubrisSystemMIBGroup.name: colubrisSystemMIBGroup
colubrisSystemMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the System MIB capability.

colubrisAdminAccessProfileGroup.name: colubrisAdminAccessProfileGroup
colubrisAdminAccessProfileGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the administrator access configuration capability.

colubrisSystemMIBDeprecatedGroup.name: colubrisSystemMIBDeprecatedGroup
colubrisSystemMIBDeprecatedGroup.description: A collection of deprecated objects providing the System MIB capability.
